{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Hear my voice, God, in my complaint. Preserve my life from fear of the enemy."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Hide me from the conspiracy of the wicked, from the noisy crowd of the ones doing evil;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "who sharpen their tongue like a sword, and aim their arrows, deadly words,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "to shoot innocent men from ambushes.\nThey shoot at him suddenly and fearlessly."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They encourage themselves in evil plans. They talk about laying snares secretly."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They say,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Who will see them?",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They plot injustice, saying, "
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "We have made a perfect plan!",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Surely man’s mind and heart are cunning."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "But God will shoot at them. They will be suddenly struck down with an arrow."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Their own tongues shall ruin them. All who see them will shake their heads."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "All mankind shall be afraid. They shall declare the work of God,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "and shall wisely ponder what he has done."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The righteous shall be glad in Yahweh, and shall take refuge in him."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "All the upright in heart shall praise him!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}